      "description": "Available is a driver-focused 2002 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This naturally aspirated masterpiece utilizes individual throttle bodies and Double VANOS variable valve timing to deliver linear power up to an 8,000 RPM redline. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a Getrag 420G six-speed manual transmission and a factory M-Variable limited-slip differential. This example is in solid mechanical health with documented subframe reinforcement and a recent VANOS overhaul, ensuring the chassis's torsional rigidity and engine's timing precision are preserved. While displaying honest patina consistent with its age, the suspension geometry remains sharp, featuring MacPherson struts up front and a multi-link rear setup for exceptional corner-exit traction. A true analog experience for the discerning technician.",
